name: South_Shore_Pure_White_Axess_5-shelf_Narrow_Bookcase
reviews: Bookcase is everything I expected for the price. Compressed, laminated wood from Canada is extremely heavy. Does not take to long to screw the pieces together. The back board needs to be ' tacked' in place. After sixty plus nails I felt like a shoe maker. Convenient size to tuck in a small corner of the kitchen area forbooks, nic-nacs and whatever. Alignment of pieces is acceptable.
This bookcase looks great and is very easy to set up. It took me maybe 15 minutes to put together, and I haven't had a problem with it at all.
Not stable, shelf clips are flimsy
Ordered this to fit a small space and it works. Not fancy but when filled with my "stuff" it looks fine.
The shelf is sturdy and worth the price. The chenille bedspread is veryPretty and good quality.
Great product, as described, went together easily
Easy to put together and very sturdy!
description:
This Axess 5-shelf narrow bookcase in pure white is ideal for your
binders, books or decorative items. It features five (5) open,
practical and accessible storage spaces, separated by two (2) fixed
and three (3) adjustable shelves that can support up to 30 pounds
each. Its refined lines harmonize seamlessly with virtually any
decor. Both functional and attractive with its sleek contemporary
styling, this bookcase is sure to enhance the look of any room in
your home. It is also available in royal cherry, chocolate, pure
black or morgan cherry finish. Narrow configuration means it can be placed in tight
  spacesDesigned to maximize storage in all the rooms of your
